Even after I was alone, I was still suffering from a fever and for hours I wasn't sure whether I was sleeping or not.

Still, my sleep seemed to come in fragments, like a fainting sleep, and I had one disjointed dream after another.

It feels like a lot of time has passed, but I don't feel like I've been able to sleep at all.

...After a while, I felt a cool breeze blow through the hut.

Perhaps I was so lonely that I was dreaming of my childhood. I felt like my mother was right beside me, nursing me.

"Mother...san..."

I woke up to the sound of my own hoarse voice coming from a throat parched with fever.

My mother is no longer with us. She just passed away the other day.

"Mother..."

Feeling an intense sense of loneliness, he forced his tired body to stand and covered his face.

