When I woke up after a nap, Konomi was gone.

Knowing Konomi, she might have gotten bored of playing "mother" once her fever went down and she felt relieved.

On the desk were the peeled skin and seeds of a tangerine, some of which had dried out.

Next to it is a tangerine that has not yet been peeled.

I bit into the Mitsubanto fruit, skin and all, to quench my thirst after waking up.

Even though I was feverish, I did something very embarrassing: crying and yelling in front of Konomi, and even missing my mother.

It's scary to be weak-minded.

However, having been able to let my feelings out in the open, I felt a lot lighter.

"Nothing good ever happens when you catch a cold."

I muttered to myself and went back to bed.

The only way to cure a cold is to sleep.

I lay in bed with my eyes closed, hoping to get better as quickly as possible so that I could return to my normal self from the next day.

